Behavioral Signal Specification v1

Purpose

This document defines the official behavioral signals used by the Mirror Identity Engine (MIE).

Behavioral Signals are observable trading behaviors. They feed the 10 dimensions of the Mirror Identity Framework (MIF).

Each signal includes:
- Definition
- Impacted dimensions
- Confidence level
- Impact
- Persistence
- Detection confidence

Behavioral Signal Weight Model v1

Impact:
- LOW
- MEDIUM
- HIGH
- CRITICAL

Persistence:
- Temporary
- Recurring
- Structural

Detection Confidence:
- Scale from 0 to 100


BS001 — Waits for Confirmation

Definition:
Detects whether the trader waits for valid confirmation before entering a trade.

Impacted Dimensions:
- Patience
- Discipline
- Execution

Confidence:
v1: Low/Medium
v2: High with trade-level data

Impact: HIGH
Persistence: Recurring
Detection Confidence v1: 45
Detection Confidence v2: 85


